==English==

===Intransitive verb phrase===
'''foul out'''

#{{basketball}} To be disqualified from further play for having committed too many [[foul]]s.
#: ''The Nimrod center has fouled out with only two points.''
#{{baseball}} To become [[out]] by hitting a [[foul ball]] which is caught
#: ''Jones '''fouled out''' to lead off the third.''

===Noun phrase===
'''foul out'''

#{{basketball}} An instance of fouling out
#: ''His '''foul out''' sat poorly with the crowd.''
#{{baseball}} An instance of fouling out
#: ''A '''foul out''' was recorded on the scorecard.''